  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - REASON: Due to its visibility from the public realm and the wider conservation area, resulting in an alien and incongruous feature at roof, the proposed roof terrace would result in harm to the visual appearance and historic character of the host building and wider Barnsbury Conservation Area. The proposal therefore is contrary to the NPPF 2019, policies D1, D4 and HC1 of the London Plan 2021, policies CS8 and CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of the Development Management Policies 2013, the guidance contained within the Urban Design Guide 2017 and the Barnsbury Conservation Area Design Guidelines.\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - REASON: The proposed scheme would provide substandard accommodation, by virtue of the layout of the unit and width of the main living areas and there are no exceptional circumstances to justify the provision of a 1 person studio unit. Therefore the proposal is contrary to policies D6 and H10 of the London Plan 2021, policy CS12 of the Core Strategy 2011, policies DM2.1, DM3.1, 3.3 and DM3.4 of Development Policies 2013 and the London Plan Housing Supplementary Planning Guidance November 2016.\r\n"
  ],
